712
00:46:18,740 --> 00:46:21,556
is a body without a soul.

713
00:46:21,620 --> 00:46:24,692
To whom would he dedicate
his conquests?

714
00:46:24,756 --> 00:46:29,268
What vision sustain him when
he sallies forth to do battle...

715
00:46:29,332 --> 00:46:33,076
with evil and with giants?

716
00:46:33,140 --> 00:46:35,636
Don Quixote,
having found his lady...

717
00:46:35,700 --> 00:46:38,068
sends Sancho Panza to her
with a missive.

718
00:46:38,132 --> 00:46:40,724
Missive? What's a missive?

719
00:46:40,788 --> 00:46:42,196
It's a sort of letter.

720
00:46:42,260 --> 00:46:44,436
He warned me to give it
only into your hands.

721
00:46:44,500 --> 00:46:46,068
Well, let's see it.

722
00:46:47,860 --> 00:46:49,396
I can't read.

723
00:46:49,460 --> 00:46:53,492
Neither can I, but my master,
foreseeing such a possibility...

724
00:46:53,556 --> 00:46:55,924
recited it to me,
so I could commit it to heart.

725
00:46:55,988 --> 00:46:57,237
What made him think
I couldn't read?

726
00:46:57,301 --> 00:46:59,157
Well, as he explained it...

727
00:46:59,221 --> 00:47:00,981
most noblewomen are so busy
with their needlework...

728
00:47:01,045 --> 00:47:02,101
Needlework?

729
00:47:02,165 --> 00:47:03,733
Embroidering banners
for their knights...

730
00:47:03,797 --> 00:47:05,749
he said they had no time
for study.

731
00:47:05,813 --> 00:47:07,125
What's it say?

732
00:47:08,789 --> 00:47:11,797
Hmm

733
00:47:11,861 --> 00:47:16,501
Most lovely sovereign
and highborn lady

734
00:47:16,565 --> 00:47:19,285
The heart of this,
thy vassal knight

735
00:47:19,349 --> 00:47:21,781
Faints for thy favor

736
00:47:21,845 --> 00:47:24,597
Oh, fairest of the fair

737
00:47:24,661 --> 00:47:27,221
Purest of the pure

738
00:47:27,285 --> 00:47:30,613
Incomparable Dulcinea

739
00:47:30,677 --> 00:47:33,493
Oh, that again!
My name is Aldonza.

740
00:47:33,557 --> 00:47:35,573
- Master calls you Dulcinea.
- Why?

741
00:47:35,637 --> 00:47:37,653
I don't know, but I can
tell you from experience...

742
00:47:37,717 --> 00:47:40,213
that knights have their own
language for everything...

743
00:47:40,277 --> 00:47:42,037
and it's better
not to ask questions.

744
00:47:42,101 --> 00:47:44,853
It only gets you into trouble.

745
00:47:44,917 --> 00:47:46,293
Ahem.

746
00:47:46,357 --> 00:47:49,173
I beg thee grant
that I may kiss

747
00:47:49,237 --> 00:47:52,469
The nethermost hem
of thy garment

748
00:47:52,533 --> 00:47:53,685
Kiss my what?

749
