792
00:49:59,126 --> 00:50:04,342
That I like him

793
00:50:04,406 --> 00:50:05,558
He doesn't make any sense.

794
00:50:05,622 --> 00:50:07,446
Well, that's because
you're not a squire.

795
00:50:07,510 --> 00:50:10,422
All right, you're a squire.
How does a squire squire?

796
00:50:10,486 --> 00:50:13,046
Well, I ride behind him...

797
00:50:13,110 --> 00:50:16,470
and he fights, and then
I pick him up off the ground.

798
00:50:16,534 --> 00:50:17,622
What do you get out of it?

799
00:50:17,686 --> 00:50:19,542
- What do I get?
- Yes.

800
00:50:19,606 --> 00:50:22,263
Plenty.
Why, already I've gotten...

801
00:50:22,327 --> 00:50:25,015
You've gotten nothing,
so why do you do it?

802
00:50:25,079 --> 00:50:28,823
I like him

803
00:50:28,887 --> 00:50:32,471
I really like him

804
00:50:32,535 --> 00:50:36,407
Pluck me naked
as a scalded chicken

805
00:50:36,471 --> 00:50:39,991
I like him

806
00:50:40,055 --> 00:50:42,807
Don't ask me

807
00:50:42,871 --> 00:50:46,487
For why or wherefore

808
00:50:46,551 --> 00:50:51,063
'Cause I don't have
a single good because

809
00:50:51,127 --> 00:50:54,583
Or therefore

810
00:50:54,647 --> 00:50:57,943
You can chop me for croquettes

811
00:50:58,007 --> 00:51:01,751
Beat my bones like castanets

812
00:51:01,815 --> 00:51:03,863
Make me freeze, make me fry

813
00:51:03,927 --> 00:51:05,463
Make me sigh, make me cry

814
00:51:05,527 --> 00:51:07,415
Still I'll yell to the sky

815
00:51:07,479 --> 00:51:09,527
Though I can't tell you why

816
00:51:09,591 --> 00:51:15,607
That I like him

817
00:51:24,823 --> 00:51:28,631
"Fairest of the fair.
Kiss the hem of thy garment."

818
00:51:32,343 --> 00:51:33,719
"Incomparable."

819
00:51:44,503 --> 00:51:45,847
"Dulcinea."

820
00:52:02,199 --> 00:52:03,415
Your Grace!

821
00:52:04,600 --> 00:52:07,256
Milady received thee?

822
00:52:08,344 --> 00:52:10,872
Oh, most fortunate of squires.

823
00:52:10,936 --> 00:52:14,776
The token. What of the token?

824
00:52:23,320 --> 00:52:26,136
Gossamer.

825
00:52:26,200 --> 00:52:28,056
Purest gossamer.

826
00:52:30,360 --> 00:52:31,544
Forgive me.

827
00:52:33,880 --> 00:52:34,968
I'm overcome.

828
00:52:37,240 --> 00:52:39,320
Oh, I am a little barber

829
00:52:39,384 --> 00:52:42,072
And I go my merry way

830
00:52:42,136 --> 00:52:44,536
With my razor and my basin

831
00:52:44,600 --> 00:52:47,832
I can always earn my pay

832
00:52:47,896 --> 00:52:49,752
Somebody approacheth!

833
00:52:49,816 --> 00:52:51,864
Though your chin
be smooth as satin

834
00:52:51,928 --> 00:52:55,032
You will need me soon, I know

835
00:52:55,096 --> 00:52:56,984
For the lord
protects his barbers

836
00:52:57,048 --> 00:53:01,112
And he makes the stubble grow

837
00:53:01,176 --> 00:53:03,608
Well, good day, gentlemen.

838
00:53:03,672 --> 00:53:05,720
It's just an ordinary traveler.

839
00:53:05,784 --> 00:53:06,904
Nay!

840
00:53:08,216 --> 00:53:11,032
See what he weareth on his head.

841
00:53:11,096 --> 00:53:13,240
By all the saints...

842
00:53:13,304 --> 00:53:16,856
there is a fortune
to be made right here.

843
00:53:18,264 --> 00:53:20,920
Arm thyself. This encounter
may be perilous.

844
00:53:20,984 --> 00:53:22,872
Oh, dear.

845
00:53:22,936 --> 00:53:25,304
If I slip
while I am shaving you

846
00:53:25,368 --> 00:53:27,992
And cut you to the quick

847
00:53:28,056 --> 00:53:30,296
You can use me as a doctor

848
00:53:30,360 --> 00:53:32,856
'Cause I also heal the sick

849
00:53:32,920 --> 00:53:36,024
Well, shall you be my...
shall you be my first to...

850
00:53:36,088 --> 00:53:38,584
You... you... you should be
my... my first...

851
00:54:00,633 --> 00:54:03,449
Oh, by the beard
of St. Anthony...

852
00:54:03,513 --> 00:54:07,481
I do believe I see before me...

853
00:54:07,545 --> 00:54:09,785
a knight...

854
00:54:09,849 --> 00:54:12,601
in full armor.

855
00:54:14,073 --> 00:54:17,785
It's ridiculous.
There aren't any knights!

856
00:54:17,849 --> 00:54:21,977
- What?
- I was wrong. Forgive me.

857
00:54:22,041 --> 00:54:26,681
Forgive me, your... your... bigness.

858
00:54:26,745 --> 00:54:29,369
I thought I'd been
touched by the sun.

859
00:54:29,433 --> 00:54:31,417
Thou wilt be touched by worse...

860
00:54:31,481 --> 00:54:34,969
unless thou surrender rapidly
that golden helmet...

861
00:54:35,033 --> 00:54:36,761
which is justly mine.

862
00:54:36,825 --> 00:54:39,065
Golden helmet?

863
00:54:46,169 --> 00:54:48,537
But this is a shaving basin.

864
00:54:48,601 --> 00:54:51,257
Shaving basin. Mister...

865
00:54:51,321 --> 00:54:54,073
I must say, Your Grace, it does
look like a shaving basin.

866
00:54:54,137 --> 00:54:58,329
Oh, oh, yes.
Yes. It's a shaving basin.

867
00:54:58,393 --> 00:55:03,865
I'm a barber. I was merely
wearing this for my head...

868
00:55:03,929 --> 00:55:08,665
to... to ward off the rays
of the sun, you see...

869
00:55:08,729 --> 00:55:11,353
so that's how your highship
made the mistake of...

870
00:55:11,417 --> 00:55:13,177
Silence!

871
00:55:13,241 --> 00:55:17,401
Knowest thou
what that really is?

872
00:55:17,465 --> 00:55:18,649
Uh-uh.

873
00:55:18,713 --> 00:55:21,593
The golden helmet of Mambrino.

874
00:55:21,657 --> 00:55:23,513
When worn
by one of noble heart...

875
00:55:23,577 --> 00:55:27,225
it rendereth him invulnerable
to all wounds.

876
00:55:27,289 --> 00:55:30,202
From what fallen knight
didst thou steal it?

877
00:55:30,266 --> 00:55:32,730
I didn't steal it.

878
00:55:32,794 --> 00:55:35,194
- Surrender it!
- Well, it cost me half a crown!

879
00:55:35,258 --> 00:55:36,602
Surrender it, or I'll split... -

880
00:55:36,666 --> 00:55:40,410
I must say, Your Grace,
it is worth half a crown.

881
00:55:41,946 --> 00:55:43,642
Peasant.

882
00:55:45,434 --> 00:55:50,906
Thou golden helmet of Mambrino

883
00:55:50,970 --> 00:55:55,578
With so illustrious a past

884
00:55:55,642 --> 00:56:00,250
Too long hast thou
been lost to glory

885
00:56:00,314 --> 00:56:05,114
But rediscovered now at last

886
00:56:05,178 --> 00:56:09,946
Golden helmet of Mambrino

887
00:56:10,010 --> 00:56:14,586
There can be no helm like thee

888
00:56:14,650 --> 00:56:17,018
Thou and I now

889
00:56:17,082 --> 00:56:19,194
Ere I die now

890
00:56:19,258 --> 00:56:24,090
Will make golden history

891
00:56:24,154 --> 00:56:26,298
I can hear the cuckoo singing

892
00:56:26,362 --> 00:56:29,210
In the cuckoo berry tree

893
00:56:29,274 --> 00:56:31,162
If he says that that's a helmet

894
00:56:31,226 --> 00:56:34,490
I suggest that you agree

895
00:56:34,554 --> 00:56:36,570
But he'll find it is not golden

896
00:56:36,634 --> 00:56:39,514
Will not make him
bold and brave

897
00:56:39,578 --> 00:56:41,914
Well, at least
he'll find it useful

898
00:56:41,978 --> 00:56:44,250
If he ever needs a shave

899
00:56:54,010 --> 00:56:57,626
Golden helmet

900
00:56:57,690 --> 00:57:00,986
Of Mambrino

901
00:57:01,050 --> 00:57:04,474
There can be no

902
00:57:04,538 --> 00:57:08,154
Helm like thee

903
00:57:08,218 --> 00:57:11,771
Thou and I now

904
00:57:11,835 --> 00:57:15,195
Ere I die now

905
00:57:15,259 --> 00:57:20,923
Will make golden

906
00:57:20,987 --> 00:57:30,875
History

907
00:58:26,075 --> 00:58:29,211
Are you saying your prayers?

908
00:58:29,275 --> 00:58:32,763
I thought you'd like
some refreshment, then supper.

909
00:58:33,915 --> 00:58:37,051
- Sir Castellano.
- Sir Knight.

910
00:58:41,211 --> 00:58:43,195
I would make a confession.

911
00:58:43,259 --> 00:58:45,339
To me?

912
00:58:48,155 --> 00:58:55,004
I would confess
I have never been dubbed knight.

913
00:58:55,068 --> 00:58:56,764
Oh. That's bad.

914
00:58:56,828 --> 00:58:59,612
But I am well qualified, milord.

915
00:58:59,676 --> 00:59:03,132
I am brave and courteous,
bold and generous...

916
00:59:03,196 --> 00:59:04,860
affable and patient.

917
00:59:04,924 --> 00:59:07,516
Yes. That's the list.

918
00:59:07,580 --> 00:59:11,612
Therefore
I would beg a boon of thee.

919
00:59:11,676 --> 00:59:14,268
Anything... within reason.

920
00:59:14,332 --> 00:59:19,036
Tonight, I will hold vigil
in the chapel of thy castle...

921
00:59:19,100 --> 00:59:23,548
and, at dawn,
receive from your hand...

922
00:59:23,612 --> 00:59:27,196
the ennobling stroke
of knighthood.

923
00:59:27,260 --> 00:59:31,740
But there's one small
difficulty... no chapel.

924
00:59:34,748 --> 00:59:38,684
- No chapel?
- That is, it's being restored.

925
00:59:38,748 --> 00:59:40,252
Now, if you wouldn't mind...

926
00:59:40,316 --> 00:59:43,484
holding your vigil
some other place?

927
00:59:43,548 --> 00:59:46,300
Here in the courtyard...

928
00:59:48,188 --> 00:59:49,564
under the stars.

929
00:59:49,628 --> 00:59:54,524
Of course. At dawn,
you shall be dubbed knight.

930
00:59:54,588 --> 00:59:55,772
Milord...

931
00:59:57,244 --> 00:59:59,324
I thank you.

932
00:59:59,388 --> 01:00:01,404
Now will you have some supper?

933
01:00:01,468 --> 01:00:04,604
Before a vigil? Nay, milord.

934
01:00:04,668 --> 01:00:09,372
On this night, I must fast
and compose my spirit.

935
01:01:34,173 --> 01:01:37,373
We have come for Don Quixote,
Knight of La Mancha.

936
01:01:37,437 --> 01:01:40,061
We have word
he stays at this inn.

937
01:01:40,125 --> 01:01:42,749
Yes, Your Grace,
he does stay here.

938
01:01:42,813 --> 01:01:46,013
My sister, this great lady
would speak with him.

939
01:01:46,077 --> 01:01:49,725
The drums sound!
Why am I summoned?

940
01:01:49,789 --> 01:01:51,261
Are you the man we seek?

941
01:01:51,325 --> 01:01:53,853
I am Don Quixote, de La Mancha.

942
01:01:53,917 --> 01:01:56,605
Fire cannot be hidden.

943
01:01:56,669 --> 01:01:59,261
Virtue cannot fail
to be recognized.

944
01:01:59,325 --> 01:02:00,925
Cease your praises.

945
01:02:00,989 --> 01:02:04,541
Word of your renown met us
on the very shores of Spain.

946
01:02:04,605 --> 01:02:07,421
You have no need
to sue for favor.

947
01:02:07,485 --> 01:02:10,333
Only say how I may help you.

948
01:02:14,205 --> 01:02:16,445
Milady, you must not kneel.

949
01:02:16,509 --> 01:02:19,166
I shall not rise until
you grant the boon I ask.

950
01:02:19,230 --> 01:02:22,206
I grant it freely.

951
01:02:23,806 --> 01:02:27,678
The Great Enchanter has brought
unhappiness to us all.

952
01:02:27,742 --> 01:02:29,598
Your enemy.

953
01:02:29,662 --> 01:02:32,638
He has bewitched our brother.

954
01:02:32,702 --> 01:02:35,198
Turned him to stone.

955
01:02:35,262 --> 01:02:37,406
He will not regain
his former self...

956
01:02:37,470 --> 01:02:40,446
until Don Quixote
joins in single combat...

957
01:02:40,510 --> 01:02:41,950
with the Enchanter.

958
01:02:48,222 --> 01:02:51,070
Have the fates
indeed reserved...

959
01:02:51,134 --> 01:02:54,494
this unparalleled adventure
for my sword?

960
01:02:56,862 --> 01:03:00,990
Assist me, sweet Dulcinea.

961
01:03:02,142 --> 01:03:04,222
Let not your favor
and protection...

962
01:03:04,286 --> 01:03:07,038
fail me in this, my first trial.

963
01:03:08,862 --> 01:03:11,166
Where shall I find
the Enchanter?

964
01:03:11,230 --> 01:03:14,270
Declare yourself,
and he will find you.

965
01:03:14,334 --> 01:03:16,478
Pray well, Don Quixote.

966
01:03:16,542 --> 01:03:20,638
Pray power into thine arm,
a keen edge to thy sword...

967
01:03:20,702 --> 01:03:23,006
and courage into thy soul.

968
01:03:23,070 --> 01:03:26,398
I shall take my prayers up
in the chapel.

969
01:03:27,838 --> 01:03:29,918
Here is my arm.

970
01:03:52,478 --> 01:03:54,622
Is this the lady Dulcinea?

971
01:03:55,838 --> 01:03:57,694
The gentleman's talking to you.

972
01:03:57,758 --> 01:04:00,895
- Ah!
- Dulcinea.

973
01:04:00,959 --> 01:04:02,623
Her name's Aldonza.

974
01:04:02,687 --> 01:04:06,751
The old gentleman, he took
a fancy to calling her Dulcinea.

975
01:04:06,815 --> 01:04:08,191
Where's this chapel?

976
01:04:08,255 --> 01:04:10,111
How does it happen
a wretched tavern like this...

977
01:04:10,175 --> 01:04:11,327
can boast a chapel?

978
01:04:11,391 --> 01:04:13,695
It isn't a chapel, Your Grace.

979
01:04:13,759 --> 01:04:15,103
He's in the stable.

980
01:04:15,167 --> 01:04:17,343
Ah, another excess
of imagination.

981
01:04:17,407 --> 01:04:18,783
How does it harm anyone?

982
01:04:18,847 --> 01:04:20,991
You're more of a fool
than he is...

983
01:04:21,055 --> 01:04:23,807
playing tricks on a man
who is mad. Leave me!

984
01:04:23,871 --> 01:04:28,991
One might say Jesus was mad...
or St. Francis.

985
01:04:29,055 --> 01:04:33,311
A man who chooses to be mad
can also choose to be sane.

986
01:04:33,375 --> 01:04:37,535
Oh, yes. It was easy enough
planning this enterprise...

987
01:04:37,599 --> 01:04:40,895
but it will be difficult
to come out of it well.

988
01:04:40,959 --> 01:04:43,871
May not the cure be more cruel
than the disease?

989
01:04:43,935 --> 01:04:46,271
We have given reality
to his madness.

990
01:04:46,335 --> 01:04:48,191
We cannot abandon him now.

991
01:04:48,255 --> 01:04:50,591
We have said
he will meet the Enchanter.

992
01:04:50,655 --> 01:04:52,287
He must meet him.

