Little bird, little bird

998
01:05:53,692 --> 01:05:58,204
Do you sing for me?

999
01:06:02,811 --> 01:06:07,707
Do you bring me word

1000
01:06:07,771 --> 01:06:12,186
Of one I know?

1001
01:06:12,250 --> 01:06:14,714
Little bird, little bird

1002
01:06:14,778 --> 01:06:17,082
I love her so

1003
01:06:17,146 --> 01:06:19,002
Little bird, little bird

1004
01:06:19,066 --> 01:06:21,402
And I have to know

1005
01:06:21,466 --> 01:06:25,241
Little bird, little bird

1006
01:06:25,305 --> 01:06:30,041
Beneath this tree

1007
01:06:30,105 --> 01:06:33,913
This cinnamon tree

1008
01:06:33,977 --> 01:06:38,200
We learned to love

1009
01:06:38,264 --> 01:06:42,104
We learned to cry

1010
01:06:42,168 --> 01:06:46,679
For here we met

1011
01:06:46,743 --> 01:06:50,359
And here we kissed

1012
01:06:50,423 --> 01:06:54,839
And here
one cold and moonless night

1013
01:06:54,903 --> 01:06:58,838
We said good-bye

1014
01:06:58,902 --> 01:07:01,398
Little bird, little bird

1015
01:07:01,462 --> 01:07:03,478
Little bird, little bird

1016
01:07:03,542 --> 01:07:05,558
Oh, have pity on me

1017
01:07:05,622 --> 01:07:07,478
Little bird, little bird

1018
01:07:07,542 --> 01:07:09,397
Bring her back to me now

1019
01:07:09,461 --> 01:07:11,541
Little bird, little bird

1020
01:07:11,605 --> 01:07:13,557
Beneath the cinnamon tree

1021
01:07:13,621 --> 01:07:15,893
Little bird, little bird

1022
01:07:15,957 --> 01:07:18,933
I have waited too long

1023
01:07:18,997 --> 01:07:20,052
Little bird

1024
01:07:20,116 --> 01:07:23,092
Without a song

1025
01:07:23,156 --> 01:07:26,228
- Little bird,
- Little bird, little bird

1026
01:07:26,292 --> 01:07:28,052
Please fly, please go

1027
01:07:28,116 --> 01:07:30,452
Little bird, little bird

1028
01:07:30,516 --> 01:07:32,435
And tell her so

1029
01:07:32,499 --> 01:07:36,691
Little bird, little bird

1030
01:07:36,755 --> 01:07:42,930
Little bird, little bird

1031
01:07:42,994 --> 01:07:45,330
- Sss!
- Awoo!

1032
01:07:45,394 --> 01:07:47,538
I spit on all your little birds!

1033
01:07:49,362 --> 01:07:50,418
Here!

1034
01:07:50,482 --> 01:07:52,306
Give it back!
Give it back to me!

1035
01:07:52,370 --> 01:07:53,458
What's this?

1036
01:07:53,522 --> 01:07:55,665
- "The most lovely sovereign...
- Oh!

1037
01:07:55,729 --> 01:07:58,257
"And high-born lady..."

1038
01:07:58,321 --> 01:08:00,209
It's from her knight!

1039
01:08:02,193 --> 01:08:04,113
It's a love letter.

1040
01:08:05,297 --> 01:08:08,336
- Such fine words.
- Well, fine words!

1041
01:08:08,400 --> 01:08:10,704
All right.
He's a man, isn't he?

1042
01:08:10,768 --> 01:08:12,912
He wants what
every other man wants. So!

1043
01:08:12,976 --> 01:08:14,608
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

1044
01:08:17,423 --> 01:08:20,431
Hey... soon?

1045
01:08:20,495 --> 01:08:22,959
When I'm through in the kitchen.

1046
01:09:30,121 --> 01:09:33,801
Now I must consider
how sages of the future...

1047
01:09:33,865 --> 01:09:36,905
will describe
this historic night.

1048
01:09:40,392 --> 01:09:44,168
Long after the sun
had retired to his couch...

1049
01:09:44,232 --> 01:09:47,720
darkening the gates
and balconies of La Mancha...

1050
01:09:47,784 --> 01:09:51,847
Don Quixote, with lofty
expression and measured tread...

1051
01:09:51,911 --> 01:09:55,623
held vigil in the courtyard
of a mighty castle.

1052
01:09:57,543 --> 01:09:59,271
Ohh.

1053
01:10:00,806 --> 01:10:04,358
Maker of empty boasts...

1054
01:10:04,422 --> 01:10:07,302
on this of all nights
to give way to vanity.

