01:10:08,902 --> 01:10:14,597
No. Don Quixote,
take a deep breath of life...

1056
01:10:14,661 --> 01:10:17,893
and consider
how it should be lived.

1057
01:10:22,821 --> 01:10:27,428
Call nothing thine
except thy soul.

1058
01:10:28,580 --> 01:10:32,836
Love not what thou art,
only what thou may become.

1059
01:10:32,900 --> 01:10:35,843
Do not pursue pleasure...

1060
01:10:35,907 --> 01:10:39,811
or thou mayest have
the misfortune to overtake it.

1061
01:10:41,539 --> 01:10:43,875
Look always forward.

1062
01:10:43,939 --> 01:10:46,146
In last year's nests...

1063
01:10:48,866 --> 01:10:52,610
there are no birds this year.

1064
01:10:54,018 --> 01:10:58,753
Be just to all men,
courteous to all women.

1065
01:10:58,817 --> 01:11:01,537
Live in the vision...

1066
01:11:01,601 --> 01:11:07,393
of the one for whom
great deeds are done...

1067
01:11:07,457 --> 01:11:08,833
Dulcinea.

1068
01:11:08,896 --> 01:11:11,392
Get up from there! Get up!

1069
01:11:11,456 --> 01:11:12,832
Milady.

1070
01:11:12,896 --> 01:11:14,432
Why do you call me
by that name?

1071
01:11:14,496 --> 01:11:17,312
- Because it is yours.
- My name is Aldonza!

1072
01:11:17,376 --> 01:11:19,392
I know you, milady.

1073
01:11:19,456 --> 01:11:21,439
I think you know me not.

1074
01:11:21,503 --> 01:11:25,471
All my years I have known you,
your nobility of spirit...

1075
01:11:25,535 --> 01:11:28,511
long have I seen you
in my heart.

1076
01:11:28,575 --> 01:11:30,943
Your heart
doesn't know much about women.

1077
01:11:31,007 --> 01:11:33,502
It knows all, milady.

1078
01:11:33,566 --> 01:11:36,094
Woman is the soul of man...

1079
01:11:36,158 --> 01:11:38,974
the radiance
that lights his way.

1080
01:11:39,038 --> 01:11:42,270
Woman is glory.

1081
01:11:43,421 --> 01:11:45,085
What do you want of me?

1082
01:11:45,149 --> 01:11:47,069
- Nothing.
- Liar.

1083
01:11:47,133 --> 01:11:48,957
I deserve the rebuke.

1084
01:11:49,021 --> 01:11:51,709
- I ask of milady...
- Now we get to it!

1085
01:11:53,245 --> 01:11:56,060
That I may be allowed
to serve her...

1086
01:11:56,124 --> 01:11:59,036
that I may hold her
in my heart...

1087
01:11:59,100 --> 01:12:02,684
that to her
I may dedicate each victory...

1088
01:12:02,748 --> 01:12:06,044
and call upon her in defeat.

1089
01:12:06,140 --> 01:12:09,755
And if at last I give my life...

1090
01:12:09,819 --> 01:12:14,075
I give it
in the sacred name of Dulcinea.

1091
01:12:15,739 --> 01:12:19,642
I must go. Pedro is waiting.

1092
01:12:19,706 --> 01:12:21,114
Why do you do these things?

1093
01:12:21,178 --> 01:12:22,874
What things?

1094
01:12:22,938 --> 01:12:25,018
These ridiculous...
the things you do.

1095
01:12:25,082 --> 01:12:28,986
I come in a world of iron...

1096
01:12:29,050 --> 01:12:31,513
to make a world of gold.

1097
01:12:31,577 --> 01:12:33,657
The world's a dung heap...

1098
01:12:33,721 --> 01:12:36,217
and we are maggots
that crawl on it.

1099
01:12:36,281 --> 01:12:38,521
No.

1100
01:12:38,585 --> 01:12:40,984
Milady knows better
in her heart.

1101
01:12:41,080 --> 01:12:44,856
What's in my heart
will get me halfway to hell...

1102
01:12:44,920 --> 01:12:46,776
and you, Señor Don Quixote...

1103
01:12:46,840 --> 01:12:49,464
your head is going to end up
a stranger to your neck.

1104
01:12:49,528 --> 01:12:52,023
- That doesn't matter.
- What does?

1105
01:12:52,087 --> 01:12:54,167
Only that I follow the quest.

1106
01:12:55,575 --> 01:12:56,983
That for your quest.

1107
01:12:59,479 --> 01:13:03,223
What does it mean... quest?

1108
01:13:03,287 --> 01:13:08,726
The mission of each true knight
is duty...

1109
01:13:08,790 --> 01:13:11,990
nay, is privilege.

1110
01:13:13,590 --> 01:13:18,485
To dream the impossible dream

1111
01:13:18,549 --> 01:13:23,285
To fight the unbeatable foe

1112
01:13:23,349 --> 01:13:28,692
To bear with unbearable sorrow

1113
01:13:28,756 --> 01:13:33,844
To run
where the brave dare not go

1114
01:13:33,908 --> 01:13:38,995
To right the unrightable wrong

1115
01:13:39,059 --> 01:13:44,403
To love
pure and chaste from afar

1116
01:13:44,467 --> 01:13:49,682
To try when your arms
are too weary

1117
01:13:49,746 --> 01:13:54,482
To reach the unreachable star

1118
01:13:54,546 --> 01:13:56,882
This is my quest

1119
01:13:56,946 --> 01:13:59,698
To follow that star

1120
01:13:59,762 --> 01:14:01,617
No matter how hopeless

1121
01:14:01,681 --> 01:14:04,497
No matter how far

1122
01:14:04,561 --> 01:14:06,897
To fight for the right

1123
01:14:06,961 --> 01:14:09,649
Without question or pause

1124
01:14:09,713 --> 01:14:11,857
To be willing
to march into hell

1125
01:14:11,921 --> 01:14:15,216
For a heavenly cause

1126
01:14:15,280 --> 01:14:19,856
And I know if I'll only be true

1127
01:14:19,920 --> 01:14:22,864
To this glorious quest

1128
01:14:22,928 --> 01:14:27,535
That my heart
will lie peaceful and calm

1129
01:14:27,599 --> 01:14:32,047
When I'm laid to my rest

1130
01:14:32,111 --> 01:14:37,614
And the world
will be better for this

1131
01:14:37,678 --> 01:14:42,894
That one man
scorned and covered with scars

1132
01:14:42,958 --> 01:14:48,973
Still strove
with his last ounce of courage

1133
01:14:49,037 --> 01:14:51,693
To reach

1134
01:14:51,757 --> 01:15:02,540
The unreachable star

1135
01:15:06,412 --> 01:15:10,603
Once, just once, would you
look at me as I really am?

1136
01:15:10,667 --> 01:15:14,539
I see beauty, purity.

1137
01:15:15,531 --> 01:15:17,291
Dulcinea.

1138
01:15:17,355 --> 01:15:21,034
You!
You keep me waiting, would you?

1139
01:15:21,098 --> 01:15:23,658
- I wasn't. I didn't mean to...
- Milady!

1140
01:15:23,722 --> 01:15:26,634
My little flower!

1141
01:15:26,698 --> 01:15:28,234
Monster!

1142
01:15:28,298 --> 01:15:29,674
Stay clear!

1143
01:15:29,738 --> 01:15:32,170
Thou wouldst strike a woman?

1144
01:15:32,234 --> 01:15:35,049
Ah, stand back,
or I'll break your head.

1145
01:15:35,113 --> 01:15:39,209
Thou heart of flint
and bowels of cork.

1146
01:15:45,768 --> 01:15:47,880
I'm killed.

1147
01:15:47,944 --> 01:15:49,480
Jose! Tenorio!

1148
01:15:49,480 --> 01:15:50,312
Jose! Tenorio!

1149
01:15:50,376 --> 01:15:53,352
- Pedro!
- Anselmo! Jose!

1150
01:15:53,416 --> 01:15:55,783
Muleteers!

1151
01:15:55,847 --> 01:15:57,191
Anselmo!

1152
01:15:58,951 --> 01:16:02,823
Tenorio! Anselmo! Muleteers!

1153
01:16:02,887 --> 01:16:04,615
Hold thou!

1154
01:16:04,679 --> 01:16:07,238
Heed the knocking
of thy craven knees!

1155
01:16:07,302 --> 01:16:08,838
Prepare to do battle!

1156
01:16:08,902 --> 01:16:11,878
Come one! Come all!

1157
01:16:13,638 --> 01:16:17,190
Come what may come!
Here am I!

1158
01:16:22,693 --> 01:16:24,965
Let him be.
He's worth a thousand of you!

1159
01:16:25,029 --> 01:16:27,205
Ahh, back, whore!
I'll show you!

1160
01:16:32,516 --> 01:16:33,828
Sancho!

1161
01:16:33,892 --> 01:16:35,012
Hold on, Your Grace!

1162
01:16:35,076 --> 01:16:36,964
Sancho!

1163
01:16:58,978 --> 01:17:00,834
Coming, Master!

1164
01:17:10,177 --> 01:17:11,905
Look out, Tenorio!

1165
01:17:14,785 --> 01:17:17,120
Help me! Help me! Help me!

1166
01:17:29,631 --> 01:17:31,167
Look out, Master! Look out!

1167
01:17:52,925 --> 01:17:54,141
Victory.

1168
01:17:54,205 --> 01:17:57,021
- Victory?
- Victory?

1169
01:17:57,085 --> 01:17:59,549
- Victory.
- Victory!

1170
01:17:59,613 --> 01:18:01,788
- Victory?
- Victory.

1171
01:18:01,852 --> 01:18:04,988
Victory! Victory!

1172
01:18:05,052 --> 01:18:05,148
What's this? All the noise?

1173
01:18:05,148 --> 01:18:07,900
What's this? All the noise?

1174
01:18:09,980 --> 01:18:12,923
- What dreadful thing?
- What glorious thing!

1175
01:18:12,987 --> 01:18:14,683
Don Castellano...

1176
01:18:14,747 --> 01:18:19,291
I would inform you
right has triumphed!

1177
01:18:19,355 --> 01:18:20,923
Your Grace, are you hurt?

1178
01:18:20,987 --> 01:18:26,138
No, no.
A little weakness... temporary.

1179
01:18:26,202 --> 01:18:27,354
Your Grace!

1180
01:18:27,418 --> 01:18:29,498
Bring water! Water, quick!

1181
01:18:32,250 --> 01:18:34,074
Oh, crusader.

1182
01:18:38,137 --> 01:18:40,345
Your Grace. Your Grace?

1183
01:18:42,233 --> 01:18:44,025
- He's coming round.
- Oh.

1184
01:18:45,081 --> 01:18:50,552
Oh, that I might always wake
unto such a vision.

1185
01:18:50,616 --> 01:18:51,704
Don't move.

1186
01:18:51,768 --> 01:18:55,320
I must say, Your Grace,
we certainly did a job out here.

1187
01:18:55,384 --> 01:18:56,472
We routed them.

1188
01:18:56,536 --> 01:18:59,159
That bunch will be
walking bow-legged for a week.

1189
01:18:59,223 --> 01:19:03,223
Milady, it is not seemly
to gloat over the fallen.

1190
01:19:03,287 --> 01:19:05,271
Let them rot in hell!

1191
01:19:06,295 --> 01:19:09,335
Sir, I am
a tame and peaceful man.

1192
01:19:09,399 --> 01:19:12,470
Please, Sir Knight, I do not
wish to be inhospitable...

1193
01:19:12,534 --> 01:19:15,798
but I must ask you to leave
as soon as you're able.

1194
01:19:15,862 --> 01:19:20,726
I am sorry to have offended
the dignity of your castle...

1195
01:19:20,790 --> 01:19:23,477
and at daylight,
I shall depart...

1196
01:19:23,541 --> 01:19:26,549
but first, may I remind you
of your promise?

1197
01:19:26,613 --> 01:19:27,989
Promise?

1198
01:19:28,053 --> 01:19:30,389
True, it is not yet dawn...

1199
01:19:30,453 --> 01:19:35,668
but I have kept vigil
and proven myself in combat.

1200
01:19:35,732 --> 01:19:39,988
I therefore beg you,
dub me knight.

1201
01:19:40,052 --> 01:19:43,540
Oh, certainly.
Let's get it over with.

1202
01:19:43,604 --> 01:19:47,379
Sancho, would you be
good enough to fetch my sword?

1203
01:19:47,443 --> 01:19:48,851
Yes, Your Grace.

1204
01:19:50,707 --> 01:19:52,595
I cannot speak, milady...

1205
01:19:52,659 --> 01:19:55,922
how joyful I am that this
ceremony should take place...

1206
01:19:55,986 --> 01:19:57,362
in your presence.

1207
01:19:57,426 --> 01:19:58,802
Be careful, now.

1208
01:19:58,866 --> 01:20:03,506
It is the solemn moment
that seals my vocation.

1209
01:20:03,570 --> 01:20:06,898
- Are you ready?
- I am.

1210
01:20:06,994 --> 01:20:09,777
Very well, then. Kneel.

1211
01:20:15,505 --> 01:20:18,161
Don Quixote de La Mancha...

1212
01:20:18,225 --> 01:20:21,040
I hereby dub thee knight.

1213
01:20:22,128 --> 01:20:23,184
My Lord.

1214
01:20:23,248 --> 01:20:25,552
Didn't I do it right?

1215
01:20:26,640 --> 01:20:29,456
If your lordship
could make some mention...

1216
01:20:29,520 --> 01:20:33,007
of the deeds I've performed
to deserve this honor...

1217
01:20:33,071 --> 01:20:35,247
Oh, of course.

1218
01:20:37,743 --> 01:20:40,303
Don Quixote de La Mancha...

1219
01:20:40,367 --> 01:20:42,222
having proved yourself
this day...

1220
01:20:42,286 --> 01:20:44,878
in glorious and terrible
combat...

1221
01:20:44,942 --> 01:20:48,206
and by my authority
as lord of this castle...

1222
01:20:48,270 --> 01:20:54,701
I hereby dub thee knight.

1223
01:20:55,821 --> 01:20:57,709
My Lord...

1224
01:20:57,805 --> 01:20:58,893
Something else?

1225
01:20:59,981 --> 01:21:01,261
If your lordship recalls...

1226
01:21:01,325 --> 01:21:04,397
it is the custom
to grant the new knight...

1227
01:21:04,460 --> 01:21:05,836
an additional name.

1228
01:21:05,900 --> 01:21:10,252
If your lordship
could devise such a name...

1229
01:21:11,820 --> 01:21:14,508
Uh, let me see.

1230
01:21:17,099 --> 01:21:18,475
Hail, Knight

1231
01:21:18,539 --> 01:21:20,907
Of the Woeful Countenance

1232
01:21:20,971 --> 01:21:24,491
Knight
of the Woeful Countenance

1233
01:21:24,555 --> 01:21:26,635
Wherever you go

1234
01:21:26,699 --> 01:21:28,234
People will know

1235
01:21:28,298 --> 01:21:30,282
Of the glorious deeds

1236
01:21:30,346 --> 01:21:34,058
Of the Knight
of the Woeful Countenance

1237
01:21:34,122 --> 01:21:36,042
Farewell and good cheer

1238
01:21:36,138 --> 01:21:38,058
Oh, my brave cavalier

1239
01:21:38,154 --> 01:21:41,993
Ride onward to glorious strife

1240
01:21:42,089 --> 01:21:43,977
I swear when you're gone

1241
01:21:44,073 --> 01:21:45,865
I'll remember you well

1242
01:21:45,929 --> 01:21:50,504
For all of the rest of my life

1243
01:21:50,568 --> 01:21:54,344
Hail, Knight
of the Woeful Countenance

1244
01:21:54,440 --> 01:21:57,384
Knight
of the Woeful Countenance

1245
01:21:57,448 --> 01:22:00,168
Wherever you go

1246
01:22:00,232 --> 01:22:01,608
Face to the foe

1247
01:22:01,672 --> 01:22:03,687
They will quail at the sight

1248
01:22:03,751 --> 01:22:07,623
Of the Knight
of the Woeful Countenance

1249
01:22:07,687 --> 01:22:09,095
Oh, valorous knight

1250
01:22:09,191 --> 01:22:11,527
Go and fight for the right

1251
01:22:11,591 --> 01:22:15,366
And battle the villains that be

1252
01:22:15,430 --> 01:22:16,966
But, oh, when you do

1253
01:22:17,030 --> 01:22:19,334
What will happen to you?

1254
01:22:19,398 --> 01:22:23,334
Thank God
I won't be there to see

1255
01:22:23,398 --> 01:22:24,933
Hail, Knight

1256
01:22:24,997 --> 01:22:26,981
- Of the Woeful Countenance
- Hail, Knight

1257
01:22:27,045 --> 01:22:28,869
- Of the Woeful Countenance
- Hail, Knight

1258
01:22:28,933 --> 01:22:31,301
Of the Woeful Countenance

1259
01:22:31,397 --> 01:22:33,285
Hail, Knight

1260
01:22:33,381 --> 01:22:37,412
Hail, Knight
of the Woeful Countenance

1261
01:22:37,476 --> 01:22:40,804
Knight
of the Woeful Countenance

1262
01:22:40,900 --> 01:22:43,268
Wherever you go

1263
01:22:43,364 --> 01:22:44,740
People will know

1264
01:22:44,804 --> 01:22:46,660
Of the glorious deeds

1265
01:22:46,724 --> 01:22:51,235
Of the Knight of the Woeful

1266
01:22:51,299 --> 01:22:55,459
Countenance

1267
01:22:55,523 --> 01:22:57,411
I thank you.

1268
01:22:57,507 --> 01:23:00,578
Well, Sir Knight,
I am going to bed.

1269
01:23:00,642 --> 01:23:03,490
And I advise you to do the same.

1270
01:23:07,362 --> 01:23:11,617
Knight
of the Woeful Countenance.

1271
01:23:11,681 --> 01:23:13,505
It's a beautiful name.

1272
01:23:13,569 --> 01:23:15,457
Come, Your Grace.
Let's get you to bed.

1273
01:23:15,521 --> 01:23:19,297
Not yet, Sancho.
I owe something to my enemies.

1274
01:23:19,361 --> 01:23:22,176
- That account's been paid.
- Not yet, milady.

1275
01:23:25,344 --> 01:23:28,288
- What?
- Nobility demands.

1276
01:23:28,352 --> 01:23:29,696
It does?

1277
01:23:29,760 --> 01:23:31,168
Yes.
Therefore I will go to them.

1278
01:23:31,232 --> 01:23:33,248
I'll go. I'll minister.

1279
01:23:33,312 --> 01:23:35,967
There is no need.

1280
01:23:37,375 --> 01:23:38,911
They were my enemies, too.

1281
01:23:44,479 --> 01:23:46,654
Oh, blessed one.

1282
01:23:46,718 --> 01:23:48,702
Come, Your Grace.
Let's get you to bed.

1283
01:23:48,766 --> 01:23:51,102
Sancho, I do envy my enemies.

1284
01:23:51,166 --> 01:23:52,542
Your Grace, you're tired.

1285
01:23:52,606 --> 01:23:54,942
No, Sancho, I feel quite well.

1286
01:23:55,006 --> 01:23:56,062
Your Grace, many a man...

1287
01:23:56,126 --> 01:23:58,173
has gone to bed in the evening
feeling well...

1288
01:23:58,237 --> 01:24:00,701
only to wake up in the morning
and find himself dead.

1289
01:24:00,765 --> 01:24:02,877
- That's a proverb.
- Yes, Your Grace.

1290
01:24:02,941 --> 01:24:04,893
- I don't approve of them.
- I know, Your Grace.

1291
01:24:10,076 --> 01:24:11,996
What in hell
do you think you're doing?

1292
01:24:12,092 --> 01:24:13,980
I'm going to minister
to your wounds.

1293
01:24:14,076 --> 01:24:17,020
- You're what?
- Nobility demands.

1294
01:24:18,812 --> 01:24:21,179
Turn over, you foxy goat!

1295
01:24:37,306 --> 01:24:38,650
You...

1296
01:25:02,616 --> 01:25:04,152
Sons of whores!

1297
01:25:04,216 --> 01:25:05,655
Let me out!

1298
01:25:14,135 --> 01:25:15,895
No!

1299
01:25:15,959 --> 01:25:17,110
Bastards!

1300
01:25:17,174 --> 01:25:19,766
Bastards! Bastards!

1301
01:25:19,830 --> 01:25:21,238
Bastards!

1302
01:25:28,629 --> 01:25:30,933
Ow! Bastards!

1303
01:25:30,997 --> 01:25:32,405
Bastards!

1304
01:25:34,357 --> 01:25:36,725
Let me go!

1305
01:25:38,581 --> 01:25:41,396
Let me go!

1306
01:25:45,172 --> 01:25:46,356
No!

1307
01:25:46,420 --> 01:25:47,668
Enough!

1308
01:25:53,139 --> 01:25:54,483
Load up. We're leaving.

1309
01:25:55,475 --> 01:25:56,819
What do we do with this?

1310
01:25:56,883 --> 01:25:59,379
We'll take it along.

1311
01:26:37,807 --> 01:26:42,063
Let these events be proof
to thee, my Sancho.

1312
01:26:42,127 --> 01:26:46,095
Nobility triumphs.
Virtue will always prevail.

1313
01:26:46,159 --> 01:26:47,823
Oh, yes, Your Grace.

1314
01:26:47,887 --> 01:26:51,182
Now, in this moment of glory...

1315
01:26:51,246 --> 01:26:54,542
do I confirm my knighthood
and my oath.

1316
01:26:54,606 --> 01:26:59,757
For all my life,
this I do swear.

1317
01:27:00,877 --> 01:27:06,381
To dream the impossible dream

1318
01:27:06,445 --> 01:27:12,300
To fight the unbeatable foe

1319
01:27:12,364 --> 01:27:17,900
To bear with unbearable sorrow

1320
01:27:17,964 --> 01:27:22,635
To run
where the brave dare not go

1321
01:27:30,571 --> 01:27:31,787
What is that?

1322
01:27:31,851 --> 01:27:34,090
One of the hazards
of this prison...

1323
01:27:34,154 --> 01:27:36,970
the brave men
of the Inquisition!

1324
01:27:37,034 --> 01:27:39,434
It means
they're coming to fetch someone.

1325
01:27:40,618 --> 01:27:43,754
Haul him off,
put the question to him.

1326
01:27:43,818 --> 01:27:46,313
Next thing he knows, he is dead.

1327
01:27:46,377 --> 01:27:49,417
They're coming for me
very possibly.

1328
01:27:49,481 --> 01:27:53,033
What, Cervantes, not afraid?
Where's your courage?

1329
01:27:53,097 --> 01:27:54,953
Or is that
in your imagination, too?

1330
01:27:55,017 --> 01:27:57,736
No escape. This is happening.

1331
01:27:57,800 --> 01:28:00,520
Not to your brave
man of La Mancha, but to you.

1332
01:28:00,584 --> 01:28:04,072
Quick, Cervantes, call on him.
Let him shield you.

1333
01:28:04,136 --> 01:28:08,551
Let him save you,
if he can... from that.

1334
01:28:56,611 --> 01:28:59,715
No! No! No! No!

1335
01:29:14,594 --> 01:29:16,993
Well, not this time.

1336
01:29:17,089 --> 01:29:18,945
But you see, Cervantes,
there is a difference...

1337
01:29:19,009 --> 01:29:20,929
between reality and illusion...

1338
01:29:21,025 --> 01:29:23,585
and a difference
between these prisoners...

1339
01:29:23,649 --> 01:29:25,313
and your men of lunacy.

1340
01:29:25,377 --> 01:29:29,184
I'd say rather men
whose illusions were very real.

1341
01:29:29,280 --> 01:29:31,648
Much the same thing,
isn't it, really?

1342
01:29:34,240 --> 01:29:37,632
Why are you poets
so fascinated with madmen?

1343
01:29:37,696 --> 01:29:39,392
We have much in common.

1344
01:29:39,456 --> 01:29:40,863
You both turn your backs
on life?

1345
01:29:40,959 --> 01:29:43,903
We both select from life!

1346
01:29:43,967 --> 01:29:47,039
A man has to come to terms
with life as it is.

1347
01:29:47,103 --> 01:29:49,471
Life as it is.

1348
01:29:49,535 --> 01:29:52,766
I have lived for over
forty years, and I've seen...

1349
01:29:54,462 --> 01:29:57,118
life as it is.

1350
01:29:59,806 --> 01:30:01,150
Pain...

1351
01:30:03,485 --> 01:30:04,701
misery...

1352
01:30:04,765 --> 01:30:06,045
cruelty beyond belief.

1353
01:30:06,109 --> 01:30:10,621
I've heard all the voices
of God's noblest creature.

1354
01:30:10,685 --> 01:30:14,588
Moans from bundles of filth
in the street.

1355
01:30:16,124 --> 01:30:19,100
I've been a soldier and a slave.

1356
01:30:20,828 --> 01:30:22,748
I've seen my comrades
fall in battle...

1357
01:30:22,844 --> 01:30:26,139
or die more slowly
under the lash in Africa.

1358
01:30:26,203 --> 01:30:28,059
I've held them
at the last moment.

1359
01:30:28,123 --> 01:30:32,859
These were men
who saw life as it is.

1360
01:30:32,923 --> 01:30:34,875
Yet they died despairing.

1361
01:30:36,283 --> 01:30:40,986
No glory, no brave last words.

1362
01:30:42,042 --> 01:30:46,810
Only their eyes,
filled with confusion...

1363
01:30:46,906 --> 01:30:49,401
questioning why.

1364
01:30:49,465 --> 01:30:54,105
I do not think they were
asking why they were dying...

1365
01:30:54,169 --> 01:30:58,521
but why they had ever lived.

1366
01:31:00,280 --> 01:31:05,016
When life itself seems lunatic,
who knows where madness lies?

1367
01:31:05,080 --> 01:31:07,416
Perhaps to be too practical
is madness.

1368
01:31:07,480 --> 01:31:09,336
To surrender dreams,
this may be madness.

1369
01:31:09,400 --> 01:31:11,575
To seek treasure
where there is only trash...

1370
01:31:11,639 --> 01:31:14,455
too much sanity may be madness!

1371
01:31:14,519 --> 01:31:16,919
And maddest of all...

1372
01:31:17,015 --> 01:31:21,271
to see life as it is
and not as it should be!

1373
01:31:21,335 --> 01:31:23,734
I am I, Don Quixote

1374
01:31:23,830 --> 01:31:26,166
The Lord of La Mancha

1375
01:31:26,230 --> 01:31:30,486
Destroyer of evil am I

1376
01:31:30,550 --> 01:31:33,142
I will march to the sound

1377
01:31:33,206 --> 01:31:35,765
Of the trumpets of glory

1378
01:31:35,829 --> 01:31:40,149
Forever to conquer or die

1379
01:31:42,549 --> 01:31:43,925
I don't understand.

1380
01:31:43,989 --> 01:31:45,876
Don't understand what,
my friend?

1381
01:31:45,972 --> 01:31:47,380
Why you're so cheerful.

1382
01:31:47,444 --> 01:31:49,780
First you find your lady,
then you lose her.

1383
01:31:49,844 --> 01:31:50,900
Never lost.

1384
01:31:50,964 --> 01:31:52,820
Well, she ran off
with those muleteers.

1385
01:31:52,884 --> 01:31:55,220
Doubtless for some high purpose.

1386
01:31:55,284 --> 01:31:57,363
High purpose
with those low characters?

1387
01:31:57,427 --> 01:32:01,683
Sancho, always thine eye sees
evil in preference to good.

1388
01:32:01,747 --> 01:32:05,363
My eye did not make this world.
It only sees it.

1389
01:32:05,427 --> 01:32:07,923
Right, and furthermore,
I think you should call a truce.

1390
01:32:07,987 --> 01:32:10,674
What, and allow wickedness
to flourish?

1391
01:32:10,738 --> 01:32:13,554
I've noticed wickedness
wears pretty thick armor.

1392
01:32:13,618 --> 01:32:15,506
And for that
would you have me cease?

1393
01:32:15,570 --> 01:32:18,450
Nay, let a man be struck down
a thousand times!

1394
01:32:18,546 --> 01:32:20,593
- Still must he rise and...
- Do battle, yes.

1395
01:32:20,657 --> 01:32:23,153
Lies, lies, lies!
Madness and lies!

1396
01:32:23,153 --> 01:32:24,849
Lies, lies, lies!
Madness and lies!

1397
01:32:36,368 --> 01:32:40,368
They shall be punished,
who did this crime.

1398
01:32:40,432 --> 01:32:42,704
Crime?

1399
01:32:42,768 --> 01:32:46,063
You know the worst crime
of all? Being born.

1400
01:32:46,159 --> 01:32:48,687
For that you get punished
your whole life.

1401
01:32:48,751 --> 01:32:51,951
- Dulcinea.
- Enough of that!

1402
01:32:52,015 --> 01:32:53,839
Get yourself to a madhouse!

1403
01:32:53,903 --> 01:32:56,238
Rave about nobility
where no one can hear.

1404
01:32:56,302 --> 01:32:59,598
- Milady.
- I'm not your lady!

1405
01:32:59,694 --> 01:33:02,990
I'm not any kind of a lady.

1406
01:33:03,086 --> 01:33:08,301
For a lady
has modest and maidenly airs

1407
01:33:08,365 --> 01:33:13,133
And a virtue a blind man
could see that I lack

1408
01:33:13,229 --> 01:33:15,917
It's hard to develop

1409
01:33:15,981 --> 01:33:18,348
These maidenly airs

1410
01:33:18,412 --> 01:33:22,124
In a stable,
laid flat on your back

1411
01:33:23,308 --> 01:33:26,124
Won't you look at me,
look at me

1412
01:33:26,188 --> 01:33:29,003
God, won't you look at me?

1413
01:33:29,067 --> 01:33:31,371
Look at the kitchen slut

1414
01:33:31,435 --> 01:33:34,059
Reeking of sweat

1415
01:33:34,123 --> 01:33:36,427
Born on a dung heap

1416
01:33:36,491 --> 01:33:38,955
To die on a dung heap

1417
01:33:39,019 --> 01:33:42,826
A strumpet men use and forget

1418
01:33:44,330 --> 01:33:46,410
If you feel that you see me

1419
01:33:46,474 --> 01:33:51,658
Not quite at my virginal best

1420
01:33:51,722 --> 01:33:54,313
Cross my palm with a coin

1421
01:33:54,377 --> 01:33:58,633
And I'll willingly
show you the rest

1422
01:33:58,697 --> 01:34:01,641
Never deny
that you are Dulcinea.

1423
01:34:01,705 --> 01:34:04,904
Take the clouds from your eyes
and see me as I really am!

1424
01:34:04,968 --> 01:34:06,984
You have shown me the sky

1425
01:34:07,048 --> 01:34:09,832
But what good is the sky

1426
01:34:09,896 --> 01:34:14,887
To a creature who'll never
do better than crawl?

1427
01:34:14,951 --> 01:34:17,735
Of all the cruel bastards

1428
01:34:17,799 --> 01:34:21,031
Who've badgered and battered me

1429
01:34:21,095 --> 01:34:24,295
You are the cruelest of all

1430
01:34:25,319 --> 01:34:30,822
Can't you see what your gentle
insanities do to me?

1431
01:34:30,886 --> 01:34:35,686
Rob me of anger
and give me despair

1432
01:34:35,782 --> 01:34:39,141
Blows and abuse I can take

1433
01:34:39,237 --> 01:34:41,093
And give back again

1434
01:34:41,157 --> 01:34:45,221
Tenderness I cannot bear

1435
01:34:45,285 --> 01:34:48,389
So please torture me now

1436
01:34:48,453 --> 01:34:53,252
With your sweet Dulcineas
no more

1437
01:34:53,348 --> 01:34:56,100
I am no one, I am nothing

1438
01:34:56,164 --> 01:35:00,483
I'm only Aldonza the whore

1439
01:35:00,579 --> 01:35:04,835
Now and forever
you are milady, Dulcinea.

1440
01:35:04,899 --> 01:35:07,491
No!

1441
01:35:20,066 --> 01:35:23,362
Master.

1442
01:35:23,457 --> 01:35:25,313
Master!

1443
01:36:02,238 --> 01:36:05,246
Is this
Don Quixote de La Mancha?

1444
01:36:05,310 --> 01:36:08,350
If it is, and he is not afraid
to look upon me...

1445
01:36:08,414 --> 01:36:10,973
let him stand forth.

1446
01:36:16,317 --> 01:36:19,261
I am Don Quixote...

1447
01:36:19,325 --> 01:36:21,948
Knight
of the Woeful Countenance.

1448
01:36:22,012 --> 01:36:24,508
Then hear me, thou charlatan.

1449
01:36:24,572 --> 01:36:28,284
Thou art no knight,
but a foolish pretender.

1450
01:36:28,348 --> 01:36:31,260
Thy pretense
is a child's mockery...

1451
01:36:31,356 --> 01:36:34,939
and thy principles
dirt beneath my feet.

1452
01:36:35,003 --> 01:36:38,331
False, graceless knight...

1453
01:36:38,427 --> 01:36:42,235
before I chastise thee,
tell me thy name.

1454
01:36:42,331 --> 01:36:44,730
Thou shalt hear it
in due course.

1455
01:36:44,826 --> 01:36:47,098
And why seekest thou me?

1456
01:36:47,162 --> 01:36:50,170
Thou called upon me,
Don Quixote.

1457
01:36:50,234 --> 01:36:53,850
Thou reviled me
and threatened me.

1458
01:36:55,577 --> 01:36:57,209
The Enchanter.

1459
01:37:00,569 --> 01:37:05,337
Behold at thy feet
the gauge of battle.

1460
01:37:16,568 --> 01:37:18,423
On what terms do we fight?

1461
01:37:18,487 --> 01:37:20,279
Choose.

1462
01:37:20,343 --> 01:37:24,983
Very well. If thou art beaten,
thy freedom is forfeit...

1463
01:37:25,047 --> 01:37:27,831
and thou must obey
my every command.

1464
01:37:28,823 --> 01:37:30,038
And thy conditions?

1465
01:37:30,102 --> 01:37:32,438
If thou livest...

1466
01:37:32,502 --> 01:37:36,854
thou shalt kneel and beg
forgiveness of milady, Dulcinea.

1467
01:37:36,918 --> 01:37:40,598
Ha!
Thy lady is an alley cat.

1468
01:37:40,662 --> 01:37:44,693
- Monster! Defend thyself!
- Halt.

1469
01:37:44,757 --> 01:37:47,253
Thou asked my name, Don Quixote.

1470
01:37:47,317 --> 01:37:49,717
Now I shall tell it.

1471
01:37:49,813 --> 01:37:53,588
I am called
the Knight of the Mirrors.

1472
01:37:57,268 --> 01:38:00,788
Look, Don Quixote.
Look in the mirror of reality...

1473
01:38:00,852 --> 01:38:03,284
and behold things
as they truly are.

1474
01:38:04,755 --> 01:38:07,475
Look, Don Quixote.

1475
01:38:09,267 --> 01:38:13,523
Look in the mirror of reality.

1476
01:38:13,619 --> 01:38:15,890
Look!
What seest thou, Don Quixote?

1477
01:38:15,954 --> 01:38:20,402
A gallant knight?
Naught but an aging fool.

1478
01:38:20,466 --> 01:38:21,842
Look, dost thou see him?

1479
01:38:21,906 --> 01:38:24,658
A madman
dressed for a masquerade.

1480
01:38:24,722 --> 01:38:26,322
A masquerade!

1481
01:38:26,386 --> 01:38:29,841
Look, Don Quixote.
See him as he truly is.

1482
01:38:29,905 --> 01:38:30,929
See the clown.

1483
01:38:31,025 --> 01:38:33,489
Look, what seest thou,
Don Quixote?

1484
01:38:33,553 --> 01:38:36,529
Look! Dost thou see him?

1485
01:38:36,593 --> 01:38:40,048
A madman! Look, Don Quixote!

1486
01:38:40,112 --> 01:38:42,224
See him as he truly is.

1487
01:38:42,288 --> 01:38:44,656
Look, Don Quixote.

1488
01:38:44,720 --> 01:38:46,576
Drown, Don Quixote.

1489
01:38:46,640 --> 01:38:49,296
Drown in the mirror.

1490
01:38:49,360 --> 01:38:53,295
Drown, Don Quixote.
Drown in the mirror.

1491
01:38:53,359 --> 01:38:57,039
Go deep. Deep. Deep.

1492
01:38:57,103 --> 01:39:01,646
Deep. Go deep. Deep.

1493
01:39:01,710 --> 01:39:03,918
The masquerade is ended.

1494
01:39:03,982 --> 01:39:08,014
Confess!
Thy lady is a trollop...

1495
01:39:08,078 --> 01:39:12,845
and thy dream the nightmare
of a disordered mind.

1496
01:39:21,357 --> 01:39:22,989
It is done.

1497
01:39:23,053 --> 01:39:26,124
Your Grace, it is Dr. Carrasco.

1498
01:39:26,188 --> 01:39:28,364
It is only Sanson Carrasco.

1499
01:39:31,276 --> 01:39:35,276
Forgive me, Señor Quijana.
It was the only way.

1500
01:39:40,651 --> 01:39:44,235
Don Miguel de Cervantes?

1501
01:39:44,299 --> 01:39:47,082
Who calls?

1502
01:39:50,058 --> 01:39:51,498
Don Miguel.

1503
01:40:02,057 --> 01:40:05,513
Cervantes! Cervantes!

1504
01:40:05,577 --> 01:40:08,649
Don Miguel de Cervantes!

1505
01:40:08,713 --> 01:40:11,272
Don Miguel de Cervantes!

1506
01:40:11,336 --> 01:40:13,576
Prepare to be summoned.

1507
01:40:13,640 --> 01:40:15,784
Summoned? By whom?

1508
01:40:15,848 --> 01:40:18,568
The judges of the Inquisition.

1509
01:40:18,632 --> 01:40:22,151
Captain? How long?

1510
01:40:22,215 --> 01:40:23,783
Soon.

1511
01:40:25,415 --> 01:40:27,623
But not yet. Good.

1512
01:40:27,687 --> 01:40:30,247
You'll just have time
to finish your story.

1513
01:40:30,311 --> 01:40:33,926
The story is finished.

1514
01:40:33,990 --> 01:40:36,806
Of course.
Quite the proper ending.

1515
01:40:36,870 --> 01:40:37,958
No, no, no!

1516
01:40:38,022 --> 01:40:39,878
I don't like this ending!

1517
01:40:39,942 --> 01:40:42,182
And I don't think
the jury likes it, either.

1518
01:40:42,246 --> 01:40:44,197
Well, then. He's failed.

1519
01:40:44,293 --> 01:40:49,061
Ah, Don Miguel de Cervantes.

1520
01:40:49,157 --> 01:40:50,501
The court
hereby sentences you...

1521
01:40:50,565 --> 01:40:51,973
- Wait!
- What for?

1522
01:40:52,069 --> 01:40:54,885
- Time. I need time.
- I'll grant you that.

1523
01:40:54,949 --> 01:40:58,148
But, uh, what about
the Inquisition?

1524
01:40:58,212 --> 01:41:02,500
A few moments only.
I'll improvise an ending.

1525
01:41:02,596 --> 01:41:07,203
A farmhouse
on the plains of La Mancha.

1526
01:41:07,267 --> 01:41:09,059
Candle.

1527
01:41:09,123 --> 01:41:11,587
A room in that house.

1528
01:41:11,651 --> 01:41:15,363
When a man who once called
himself Don Quixote...

1529
01:41:15,427 --> 01:41:21,986
lies in the shadows
between living and dying.

1530
01:41:41,472 --> 01:41:43,136
Can you do nothing?

1531
01:41:43,200 --> 01:41:47,232
I'm afraid there will be no
need of my services as a doctor.

1532
01:41:52,416 --> 01:41:54,655
Where is he, I wonder?

1533
01:41:54,719 --> 01:41:58,431
In what dark cavern
of the mind?

1534
01:41:58,495 --> 01:42:02,751
- According to recent theory...
- Oh, Doctor, please.

1535
01:42:02,815 --> 01:42:05,150
Don't you think I did right?

1536
01:42:05,214 --> 01:42:07,102
There's the contradiction.

1537
01:42:09,278 --> 01:42:10,750
You again!

1538
01:42:10,846 --> 01:42:13,566
- Tell him to go away.
- What harm can he do?

1539
01:42:13,630 --> 01:42:14,878
It's all been done.

1540
01:42:14,942 --> 01:42:17,789
Your reverence?
Could I talk to him?

1541
01:42:17,885 --> 01:42:20,061
I'm afraid
he won't be able to hear you.

1542
01:42:20,125 --> 01:42:21,533
Well, then, I won't say much.

1543
01:42:25,469 --> 01:42:27,868
No mention of knight-errantry.

1544
01:42:27,964 --> 01:42:31,164
Oh, no. One does not speak
of the rope...

1545
01:42:31,228 --> 01:42:33,564
in the house of the hanged.

1546
01:42:33,628 --> 01:42:36,476
Proverb. Excuse me, Your Grace.

1547
01:42:36,572 --> 01:42:39,483
- Your Grace?
- Just a few words.

1548
01:42:39,579 --> 01:42:43,035
Little ones...
to lighten his heart.

1549
01:42:43,099 --> 01:42:46,555
A little gossip

1550
01:42:46,619 --> 01:42:48,475
A little chat

1551
01:42:48,539 --> 01:42:52,666
A little idle talk
of this and that

1552
01:42:52,730 --> 01:42:55,930
I'll tell him
all the troubles I have had

1553
01:42:55,994 --> 01:42:58,394
And since he doesn't hear

1554
01:42:58,490 --> 01:43:00,538
At least he won't feel bad

1555
01:43:00,602 --> 01:43:02,009
Shh, shh.

1556
01:43:02,073 --> 01:43:05,369
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1557
01:43:07,001 --> 01:43:09,337
Oh, what a time
I've been having...

1558
01:43:09,401 --> 01:43:11,193
since I got back, Your Grace.

1559
01:43:11,257 --> 01:43:13,656
You know my wife Teresa,
how strong she is...

1560
01:43:13,752 --> 01:43:14,968
muscles like a bull.

1561
01:43:15,032 --> 01:43:16,632
Well, she beat me.

1562
01:43:16,696 --> 01:43:19,672
She hit me with everything
but the house itself.

1563
01:43:19,736 --> 01:43:21,176
And she yells at me...

1564
01:43:21,272 --> 01:43:23,576
"Where's all the gold
and all the jewels...

1565
01:43:23,640 --> 01:43:24,823
"you were going to bring back?

1566
01:43:24,887 --> 01:43:27,927
"Where's that kingdom
you were going to conquer?"

1567
01:43:27,991 --> 01:43:30,775
Well, I kept a dignified
silence, Your Grace...

1568
01:43:30,839 --> 01:43:33,815
because there are some
questions you just can't answer.

1569
01:43:33,879 --> 01:43:37,654
Like when a man yells, "What
are you doing with my wife?"

1570
01:43:37,718 --> 01:43:41,974
That's a question
you just can't answer.

1571
01:43:42,038 --> 01:43:43,734
Of course, I hit her back,
Your Grace.

1572
01:43:43,798 --> 01:43:46,518
But she's a lot harder
than I am...

1573
01:43:46,582 --> 01:43:48,565
and as the saying goes...

1574
01:43:48,661 --> 01:43:50,869
"Whether the stone
hits the pitcher...

1575
01:43:50,933 --> 01:43:52,085
"or the pitcher
hits the stone...

1576
01:43:52,149 --> 01:43:55,381
"it's going to be bad
for the pitcher."

1577
01:43:55,445 --> 01:43:59,124
So I've got bruises
from here to...

1578
01:44:10,419 --> 01:44:17,619
Oh, I haven't fought
a windmill in a fortnight

1579
01:44:17,715 --> 01:44:21,746
And the humble joys
get duller every day

1580
01:44:21,810 --> 01:44:26,834
Why, when I'm asleep, a dragon
with his fiery tongue a-waggin'

1581
01:44:26,898 --> 01:44:31,570
Whispers, Sancho, won't you
please come out and play?

1582
01:44:31,634 --> 01:44:32,690
That's enough!

1583
01:44:32,754 --> 01:44:33,777
- What did I do?
- I warned you.

1584
01:44:33,873 --> 01:44:37,041
- I didn't do anything. I was...
- Please be quiet.

1585
01:44:40,401 --> 01:44:42,769
My friend?

1586
01:44:42,833 --> 01:44:45,520
Did Your Grace say something?

1587
01:44:49,264 --> 01:44:53,072
You are a fat pudding...

1588
01:44:53,168 --> 01:44:55,440
stuffed with proverbs.

1589
01:44:55,504 --> 01:45:00,143
Oh, that's very well-known,
Your Grace.

1590
01:45:00,207 --> 01:45:02,031
Well, as I was saying...

1591
01:45:02,095 --> 01:45:05,551
- Uncle?
- My dear.

1592
01:45:11,854 --> 01:45:14,734
Good morning, Father.

1593
01:45:14,830 --> 01:45:16,654
Or is it evening?

1594
01:45:18,318 --> 01:45:19,917
How do you feel, sir?

1595
01:45:22,605 --> 01:45:24,973
I am but well.

1596
01:45:25,037 --> 01:45:27,373
Can you speak your name?

1597
01:45:27,437 --> 01:45:29,805
Should a man not know his name?

1598
01:45:29,869 --> 01:45:33,164
If you would just say it.

1599
01:45:33,228 --> 01:45:35,756
Alonso Quijana.

1600
01:45:40,716 --> 01:45:42,603
Father?

1601
01:45:42,699 --> 01:45:46,283
I am here, beside you.

1602
01:45:46,347 --> 01:45:49,643
I wish to make a will.

1603
01:45:49,739 --> 01:45:53,386
Yes.

1604
01:45:53,450 --> 01:45:54,634
Of course.

1605
01:45:57,834 --> 01:46:00,426
- Uncle?
- Forgive me.

1606
01:46:00,490 --> 01:46:05,737
L... When I close my eyes,
I see a pale horse...

1607
01:46:05,833 --> 01:46:08,169
and I am bid mount him.

1608
01:46:08,233 --> 01:46:10,185
No, uncle, you will get well.

1609
01:46:10,281 --> 01:46:13,513
Oh, my dear master's worship,
do not die...

1610
01:46:13,577 --> 01:46:15,305
but live on many years.

1611
01:46:15,369 --> 01:46:17,896
Dying is such a waste
of good health.

1612
01:46:17,960 --> 01:46:22,600
Soft and fair, my dear ones.

1613
01:46:22,664 --> 01:46:27,016
In last year's nests,
there are no birds this year.

1614
01:46:27,112 --> 01:46:28,999
Come closer.

1615
01:46:33,543 --> 01:46:38,535
I have dreamed so strangely.

1616
01:46:38,599 --> 01:46:42,470
Oh, such dreams.

1617
01:46:42,566 --> 01:46:50,150
I... thought
I had declared myself a...

1618
01:46:52,997 --> 01:46:58,053
No, I dare not tell you,
lest you think me mad.

1619
01:46:58,117 --> 01:47:02,468
- Put them from your mind.
- They are gone.

1620
01:47:02,564 --> 01:47:06,116
Nor do I know what they meant.

1621
01:47:07,908 --> 01:47:09,060
Father?

1622
01:47:10,436 --> 01:47:14,563
Just speak, and I shall write.

1623
01:47:16,899 --> 01:47:22,019
I, Alonso Quijana...

1624
01:47:22,083 --> 01:47:24,451
with one foot in the stirrup...

1625
01:47:24,515 --> 01:47:27,842
and all too ready
for the final ride...

1626
01:47:28,930 --> 01:47:30,306
Don't admit anyone.

1627
01:47:30,370 --> 01:47:36,385
Do hereby make the following
disposition of my estate.

1628
01:47:37,953 --> 01:47:43,969
The bulk I leave to my beloved
niece Antonia Quijana...

1629
01:47:44,033 --> 01:47:48,224
with the exception
of certain personal bequests...

1630
01:47:48,288 --> 01:47:49,696
which are as follows...

1631
01:47:49,792 --> 01:47:52,640
I will allow nobody
into that room!

1632
01:47:52,736 --> 01:47:54,400
Get out of the way, you hag!

1633
01:47:54,464 --> 01:47:57,728
- What is that, Sanson?
- It's that slut from the inn.

1634
01:47:59,295 --> 01:48:01,855
I tried to stop her,
and she threatened to...

1635
01:48:01,919 --> 01:48:05,055
Tear your eyes out
if you touch me again, by God!

1636
01:48:05,119 --> 01:48:07,231
- Get out!
- Not before I see him!

1637
01:48:07,295 --> 01:48:09,087
Let her be.

1638
01:48:09,151 --> 01:48:13,278
In my house
there will be courtesy!

1639
01:48:19,006 --> 01:48:20,798
Come closer, girl.

1640
01:48:30,781 --> 01:48:33,309
What is it you wish?

1641
01:48:34,332 --> 01:48:36,124
Don't you know me?

1642
01:48:38,140 --> 01:48:39,356
Should I?

1643
01:48:41,404 --> 01:48:43,164
I am Aldonza.

1644
01:48:43,228 --> 01:48:48,379
I'm so sorry. L... I don't recall
anyone of that name.

1645
01:48:48,443 --> 01:48:50,395
Oh, please, My Lord.

1646
01:48:50,491 --> 01:48:52,987
Why do you say, "My Lord"?

1647
01:48:53,051 --> 01:48:55,899
You are My Lord, Don Quixote.

1648
01:48:57,178 --> 01:48:59,962
Don Quixote?

1649
01:49:03,258 --> 01:49:08,153
Forgive me.
I am confused by shadows.

1650
01:49:08,217 --> 01:49:12,889
It is possible I knew you once.
I do not remember.

1651
01:49:17,465 --> 01:49:18,553
This way.

1652
01:49:19,672 --> 01:49:20,952
Please try to remember.

1653
01:49:23,192 --> 01:49:26,200
Is it so important?

1654
01:49:26,264 --> 01:49:28,600
Everything.

1655
01:49:28,664 --> 01:49:30,776
My whole life.

1656
01:49:30,840 --> 01:49:33,367
You spoke to me.

1657
01:49:33,431 --> 01:49:37,143
And everything was... different.

1658
01:49:37,207 --> 01:49:39,895
I spoke to you?

1659
01:49:39,959 --> 01:49:42,774
And you looked at me...

1660
01:49:42,838 --> 01:49:46,518
and you called me
by another name.

1661
01:49:46,582 --> 01:49:48,310
Dulcinea.

1662
01:49:50,646 --> 01:49:53,590
Dulcinea

1663
01:49:55,477 --> 01:49:57,365
Once you found a girl

1664
01:49:57,429 --> 01:49:58,869
And called her

1665
01:49:58,965 --> 01:50:02,517
Dulcinea

1666
01:50:03,829 --> 01:50:06,612
When you spoke the name

1667
01:50:06,676 --> 01:50:12,372
An angel seemed to whisper

1668
01:50:12,436 --> 01:50:16,755
Dulcinea

1669
01:50:19,379 --> 01:50:21,491
Dulcinea

1670
01:50:31,730 --> 01:50:36,082
Then perhaps it was not a dream.

1671
01:50:36,178 --> 01:50:38,546
You spoke of a dream...

1672
01:50:38,610 --> 01:50:40,017
and about the quest.

1673
01:50:40,113 --> 01:50:42,097
A quest?

1674
01:50:42,193 --> 01:50:44,081
How you must fight?

1675
01:50:44,145 --> 01:50:47,313
And it doesn't matter
whether you win or lose...

1676
01:50:47,377 --> 01:50:51,152
if only you follow the quest.

1677
01:50:51,216 --> 01:50:54,544
What did I say to you?

1678
01:50:54,640 --> 01:50:56,240
Tell me the words.

1679
01:50:56,304 --> 01:51:00,560
"To dream...

1680
01:51:00,624 --> 01:51:03,247
"the impossible dream."

1681
01:51:05,295 --> 01:51:07,183
But they are your own words.

1682
01:51:07,247 --> 01:51:10,127
"To fight...

1683
01:51:10,223 --> 01:51:13,039
"the unbeatable foe."

1684
01:51:13,103 --> 01:51:14,734
Don't you remember?

1685
01:51:14,798 --> 01:51:17,646
"To bear...

1686
01:51:17,710 --> 01:51:21,102
"with unbearable sorrow."

1687
01:51:21,198 --> 01:51:23,086
You must remember!

1688
01:51:26,637 --> 01:51:29,421
"To run...

1689
01:51:29,485 --> 01:51:32,301
"where the brave dare not go."

1690
01:51:35,853 --> 01:51:37,932
To right...

1691
01:51:37,996 --> 01:51:41,036
the unrightable wrong.

1692
01:51:41,100 --> 01:51:42,860
Yes.

1693
01:51:45,548 --> 01:51:47,244
To love...

1694
01:51:47,308 --> 01:51:50,443
pure and chaste from afar.

1695
01:51:50,507 --> 01:51:52,139
Yes.

1696
01:51:52,203 --> 01:51:57,291
To try
when your arms are too weary.

1697
01:51:58,923 --> 01:52:03,498
To reach the unreachable star.

1698
01:52:03,562 --> 01:52:06,602
Thank you, My Lord.

1699
01:52:09,578 --> 01:52:12,297
Milady! This is not seemly.

1700
01:52:12,361 --> 01:52:13,769
On your knees to me?

1701
01:52:13,865 --> 01:52:16,681
- But, My Lord, you're not well.
- Not well?

1702
01:52:16,745 --> 01:52:20,073
What is sickness
to the body of a knight-errant?

1703
01:52:20,169 --> 01:52:23,624
What matter wounds?
For each time he falls...

1704
01:52:23,688 --> 01:52:27,848
he will rise again...
and woe to the wicked!

1705
01:52:27,912 --> 01:52:30,600
- Sancho?
- Here, Your Grace!

1706
01:52:30,664 --> 01:52:33,928
- My armor, my sword!
- More misadventures!

1707
01:52:33,992 --> 01:52:36,775
Adventures, old friend!

1708
01:52:36,839 --> 01:52:39,463
Oh, the trumpets of glory

1709
01:52:39,527 --> 01:52:41,639
Now call me to rise

1710
01:52:41,703 --> 01:52:46,438
Yes, the trumpets
are calling to me

1711
01:52:46,502 --> 01:52:48,646
And wherever I ride

1712
01:52:48,710 --> 01:52:51,526
Ever staunch at my side

1713
01:52:51,590 --> 01:52:56,326
My squire and my lady will be

1714
01:52:56,390 --> 01:52:59,109
I am I, Don Quixote

1715
01:52:59,173 --> 01:53:01,317
The Lord of La Mancha

1716
01:53:01,381 --> 01:53:05,541
Our destiny calls, and we go

1717
01:53:05,605 --> 01:53:08,325
And the wild winds of fortune

1718
01:53:08,389 --> 01:53:10,820
Will carry us onward

1719
01:53:10,916 --> 01:53:16,324
Whithersoever they blow

1720
01:53:16,388 --> 01:53:21,123
Whithersoever they blow

1721
01:53:21,219 --> 01:53:25,187
Onward to glory we go

1722
01:53:26,179 --> 01:53:28,579
Master!

1723
01:53:28,675 --> 01:53:30,467
- Master!
- Uncle!

1724
01:53:31,874 --> 01:53:33,154
Master.

1725
01:53:33,218 --> 01:53:35,170
My Lord.

1726
01:54:07,519 --> 01:54:16,095
De profundis clamo ad te

1727
01:54:16,191 --> 01:54:19,966
Domine

1728
01:54:20,030 --> 01:54:24,062
Domine

1729
01:54:24,126 --> 01:54:31,773
Audi vocem meam

1730
01:54:31,869 --> 01:54:39,901
Fiant aures tuae intentae

1731
01:54:39,965 --> 01:54:51,707
Ad vocem abse creationis meae

1732
01:54:51,771 --> 01:55:01,083
Si delictarum memorium

1733
01:55:01,147 --> 01:55:05,530
Serva neris

1734
01:55:08,954 --> 01:55:13,018
Domine

1735
01:55:13,082 --> 01:55:17,209
Domine...

1736
01:55:27,128 --> 01:55:29,976
He is dead.

1737
01:55:30,072 --> 01:55:33,432
My master is dead.

1738
01:55:33,528 --> 01:55:36,216
A man died.

1739
01:55:36,280 --> 01:55:39,575
He seemed a good man...

1740
01:55:39,671 --> 01:55:41,783
but I did not know him.

1741
01:55:43,607 --> 01:55:46,327
But you saw.

1742
01:55:46,391 --> 01:55:48,982
Don Quixote's not dead.

1743
01:55:49,046 --> 01:55:50,998
Believe, Sancho.

1744
01:55:51,094 --> 01:55:53,462
Believe.

1745
01:55:53,558 --> 01:55:55,542
Aldonza...

1746
01:55:59,158 --> 01:56:00,533
Dulcinea.

1747
01:56:05,109 --> 01:56:06,869
Dulcinea.

1748
01:57:10,351 --> 01:57:13,199
Under authority of the Holy
Office of the Inquisition...

1749
01:57:13,263 --> 01:57:15,119
by reason of certain offenses...

1750
01:57:15,183 --> 01:57:17,935
committed against His Majesty's
Most Catholic Church...

1751
01:57:17,999 --> 01:57:21,134
the following is summoned
to give answer...

1752
01:57:21,198 --> 01:57:23,438
and submit his person
for purification...

1753
01:57:23,502 --> 01:57:24,974
if it be so ordered...

1754
01:57:25,070 --> 01:57:28,398
Don Miguel de Cervantes.

1755
01:57:33,069 --> 01:57:36,941
I am a popular defendant.

1756
01:57:37,037 --> 01:57:39,181
Summoned before one court...

1757
01:57:39,245 --> 01:57:41,389
before I've quite finished
with another.

1758
01:57:42,893 --> 01:57:47,340
Well, what says this jury?

1759
01:57:58,891 --> 01:58:04,171
You know, I think I know now
what this contains.

1760
01:58:08,938 --> 01:58:12,138
The history of your mad knight.

1761
01:58:14,890 --> 01:58:17,418
As much as is written.

1762
01:58:17,482 --> 01:58:22,057
Read as well there
as you did here...

1763
01:58:22,121 --> 01:58:23,401
and you may not burn.

1764
01:58:25,609 --> 01:58:28,489
I have no intention of burning.

1765
01:58:32,488 --> 01:58:35,560
Cervantes?

1766
01:58:35,624 --> 01:58:38,760
I think Don Quixote...

1767
01:58:38,824 --> 01:58:41,671
is brother to Cervantes.

1768
01:58:46,311 --> 01:58:50,567
God help us.
We are both men of La Mancha.

1769
01:58:58,918 --> 01:59:03,909
For me alone
was Don Quixote born...

1770
01:59:03,973 --> 01:59:06,341
and I for him.

1771
01:59:09,605 --> 01:59:12,261
I give him to you.

1772
01:59:16,484 --> 01:59:18,212
Ready, old friend?

1773
01:59:28,387 --> 01:59:29,443
Courage.

1774
02:00:02,688 --> 02:00:07,584
To dream the impossible dream...

1775
02:00:07,648 --> 02:00:12,959
to fight the unbeatable foe.

1776
02:00:13,055 --> 02:00:18,303
To bear with unbearable sorrow

1777
02:00:18,399 --> 02:00:24,958
To run
where the brave dare not go

1778
02:00:25,022 --> 02:00:31,198
To run
where the brave dare not go

1779
02:00:31,294 --> 02:00:36,861
Though the goal
be forever too far

1780
02:00:36,925 --> 02:00:42,909
To try
though you're wayworn and weary

1781
02:00:42,973 --> 02:00:48,444
To reach the unreachable star

1782
02:00:48,508 --> 02:00:55,612
To reach the unreachable star

1783
02:00:55,676 --> 02:01:01,371
Though you know
it's impossibly high

1784
02:01:01,435 --> 02:01:07,675
To live with your heart
striving upward

1785
02:01:07,771 --> 02:01:11,066
To a far

1786
02:01:11,130 --> 02:01:15,162
Unattainable

1787
02:01:15,226 --> 02:01:22,233
Star

